et, and (ii) the amount determined under paragraph (7) for that qualified retiree.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8c37b1f-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1414/c/9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9"},"text":"(9)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Calendar year 2012","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For a month during 2012, the amount of retired pay payable to a qualified retiree is the sum of—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8c37b20-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1414/c/9/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the amount determined under paragraph (8) for that qualified retiree; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8c37b21-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1414/c/9/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" 80 percent of the difference between (i) the current baseline offset, and (ii) the amount determined under paragraph (8) for that qualified retiree.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8c37b22-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1414/c/10"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"10"},"text":"(10)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Calendar year 2013","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For a month during 2013, the amount of retired pay payable to a qualified retiree is the sum of—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8c37b23-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1414/c/10/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the amount determined under paragraph (9) for that qualified retiree; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8c37b24-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1414/c/10/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" 90 percent of the difference between (i) the current baseline offset, and (ii) the amount determined under paragraph (9) for that qualified retiree.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8c37b25-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1414/c/11"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"11"},"text":"(11)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"General limitation","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Retired pay determined under this subsection for a qualified retiree, if greater than the amount of retired pay otherwise applicable to that qualified retiree, shall be reduced to the amount of retired pay otherwise applicable to that qualified retiree.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida8c37b26-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1414/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Coordination With Combat-Related Special Compensation Program.—","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8c37b27-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1414/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In general","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"A person who is a qualified retiree under this section and is also an eligible combat-related disabled uniformed services retiree under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1413a"},"text":"section 1413a of this title","children":[],"tail":" may receive special compensation in accordance with that section or retired pay in accordance with this section, but not both."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8c37b28-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1414/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Annual open season","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary concerned shall provide for an annual period (referred to as an “open season”) during which a person described in paragraph (1) shall have the right to make an election to change from receipt of special compensation in accordance with ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1413a"},"text":"section 1413a of this title","children":[],"tail":" to receipt of retired pay in accordance with this section, or the reverse, as the case may be. Any such election shall be made under regulations prescribed by the Secretary concerned. Such regulations shall provide for the form and manner for making such an election and shall provide for the date as of when such an election shall become effective. In the case of the Secretary of a military department, such regulations shall be subject to approval by the Secretary of Defense."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida8c5ec29-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1414/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Definitions","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this section:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8c5ec2a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1414/e/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Retired pay","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The term “retired pay” includes retainer pay, emergency officers’ retirement pay, and naval pension.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8c5ec2b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1414/e/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Veterans’ disability compensation","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The term “veterans’ disability compensation” has the meaning given the term “compensation” in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s101/13"},"text":"section 101(13) of title 38","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8c5ec2c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1414/e/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Disability rated as total","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The term “disability rated as total” means—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8c5ec2d-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1414/e/3/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a disability, or combination of disabilities, that is rated as total under the standard schedule of rating disabilities in use by the Department of Veterans Affairs; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8c5ec2e-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1414/e/3/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a disability, or combination of disabilities, for which the scheduled rating is less than total but for which a rating of total is assigned by reason of inability of the disabled person concerned to secure or follow a substantially gainful occupation as a result of disabilities for which veterans’ disability compensation may be paid.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8c5ec2f-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1414/e/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Current baseline offset.—","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8c5ec30-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1414/e/4/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In general","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The term “current baseline offset” for any qualified retiree means the amount for any month that is the lesser of—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"ida8c5ec31-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1414/e/4/A/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the amount of the applicable monthly retired pay of the qualified retiree for that month; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"ida8c5ec32-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1414/e/4/A/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the amount of monthly veterans’ disability compensation to which the qualified retiree is entitled for that month.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8c5ec33-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s1414/e/4/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Applicable retired pay","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"In subparagraph (A), the term “applicable retired pay” for a qualified retiree means the amount of monthly retired pay to which the qualified retiree is entitled, determined without regard to this section or sections 5304 and 5305 of title 38, except that in the case of such a retiree who was retired under chapter 61 of this title, such amount is the amount of retired pay to which the member would have been entitled under any other provision of law based upon the member’s service in the uniformed services if the member had not been retired under chapter 61 of this title.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"ida8c5ec34-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/107/dA/tVI/s641/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–107, div. A, title VI, § 641(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2001-12-28"},"text":"Dec. 28, 2001","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/115/1149"},"text":"115 Stat. 1149","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/136/dA/tVI/s641/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–136, div. A, title VI, § 641(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2003-11-24"},"text":"Nov. 24, 2003","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/117/1511"},"text":"117 Stat. 1511","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/375/dA/tVI/s642"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–375, div. A, title VI, § 642","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-10-28"},"text":"Oct. 28, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/1957"},"text":"118 Stat. 1957","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/163/dA/tVI/s663"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–163, div. A, title VI, § 663","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-01-06"},"text":"Jan. 6, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/119/3316"},"text":"119 Stat. 3316","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/181/dA/tVI/s642/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–181, div. A, title VI, § 642(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-01-28"},"text":"Jan. 28, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/157"},"text":"122 Stat. 157","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/76/dC/tX/s10001/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–76, div. C, title X, § 10001(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-01-17"},"text":"Jan. 17, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/151"},"text":"128 Stat. 151","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/92/dA/tVI/s631/d/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–92, div. A, title VI, § 631(d)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2015-11-25"},"text":"Nov. 25, 2015","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/129/845"},"text":"129 Stat. 845","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"ida8c5ec35-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"ida8c5ec36-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"ida8c5ec37-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2015—Subsec. (b)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/92/s631/d/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–92, § 631(d)(2)","children":[],"tail":", which was approved "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2015-11-25"},"text":"Nov. 25, 2015","children":[],"tail":", provided that the amendment made by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/76/s10001/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–76, § 10001(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", which was effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2015-12-01"},"text":"Dec. 1, 2015","children":[],"tail":", would not take effect. See 2014 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2014—Subsec. (b)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/76/s10001/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–76, § 10001(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", which directed insertion of “(but without the application of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1401a/b/4"},"text":"section 1401a(b)(4) of this title","children":[],"tail":")” after “under any other provision of law”, did not take effect pursuant to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/92/s631/d/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–92, § 631(d)(2)","children":[],"tail":". See 2015 Amendment note above."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2008—Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/181"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–181","children":[],"tail":" substituted “except that payment of retired pay is subject to subsection (c) only during the period beginning on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 2004","children":[],"tail":", and ending on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 2004","children":[],"tail":", in the case of the following:” for “except that in the case of a qualified retiree receiving veterans’ disability compensation for a disability rated as 100 percent, payment of retired pay to such veteran is subject to subsection (c) only during the period beginning on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 2004","children":[],"tail":", and ending on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 2004","children":[],"tail":", and in the case of a qualified retiree receiving veterans’ disability compensation at the rate payable for a 100 percent disability by reason of a determination of individual unemployability, payment of retired pay to such veteran is subject to subsection (c) only during the period beginning on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 2004","children":[],"tail":", and ending on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 2009","children":[],"tail":".” and added subpars. (A) and (B)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2006—Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/163"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–163","children":[],"tail":" inserted “, and in the case of a qualified retiree receiving veterans’ disability compensation at the rate payable for a 100 percent disability by reason of a determination of individual unemployability, payment of retired pay to such veteran is subject to subsection (c) only during the period beginning on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 2004","children":[],"tail":", and ending on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 2009","children":[],"tail":"” before period at end."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2004—Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/375/s642/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–375, § 642(a)","children":[],"tail":", inserted before period at end “, except that in the case of a qualified retiree receiving veterans’ disability compensation for a disability rated as 100 percent, payment of retired pay to such veteran is subject to subsection (c) only during the period beginning on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 2004","children":[],"tail":", and ending on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 2004","children":[],"tail":"”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/375/s642/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–375, § 642(b)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “that pursuant to the second sentence of subsection (a)(1) is subject to this subsection” after “a qualified retiree” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2003—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/136"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–136","children":[],"tail":" amended section generally. Prior to amendment, section related to members eligible for retired pay who had service-connected disabilities: payment of r